    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for pcs.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 9.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The pcs packages provide a command-line configuration system for the Pacemaker and Corosync utilities.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* lodash: prototype pollution in _.unset and _.omit functions (CVE-2025-13465)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
